[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = MVBernoulli","category":"page"},{"location":"#MVBernoulli","page":"Home","title":"MVBernoulli","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for MVBernoulli.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [MVBernoulli]","category":"page"},{"location":"#MVBernoulli.MultivariateBernoulli","page":"Home","title":"MVBernoulli.MultivariateBernoulli","text":"MultivariateBernoulli{T}\n\nA type for representing a multivariate Bernoulli distribution.\n\nFields\n\ntabulation::Vector{T}\nordinary_moments::Vector{T}\nnormalized_moments::Vector{T}\nm::Int: the number of variables\n\nDescription\n\nFor a multivariate Bernoulli distribution with m variables, the tabulation is a vector of length 2^m containing the probabilities of each of the possible outcomes.\n\nThe ordinary moments are the expected values of the variables and of their products.\n\nmathbbEleftprod_i in I X_iright\n\nwhere I is a subset of 1:m.\n\nThe normalized moments are\n\nmathbbEleftprod_i in I (X_i - mathbbEX_i)right\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"}]
